# AiOS maintainer release-signing keys (SSH allowed-signers format).
#
# When a manifest in packages/ sets `signed = true`, `pac install`/`upgrade`
# refuse to build unless the source repo's pinned `rev` is a git tag carrying
# an SSH signature from one of the keys below. `pac` enforces this with
# `git verify-tag` under `gpg.format=ssh`, passing this file as the
# allowedSignersFile; a missing, unsigned, or unlisted-key tag fails the
# install before any build runs.
#
# Field 1 is the principal: the email git records as the *tagger* on a signed
# release tag (so it must match `git config user.email` at signing time).
# The key is the dedicated Ed25519 release-signing key "aios-maintainer-signing",
# kept separate from any authentication key.
